<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be in the race • make the race</xh5><p> <i>be in the race—</i>1. compete for smth. such as public office, etc.: Morris Udall, the “liberal-progressive” spear carrier, will have to win to stay <u>in the race</u>. 2. <i>(negat.)</i> not have a chance of winning or obtaining smth.: A few years ago he wouldn’t have <u>been in the race</u> to own a car like that.</p><p> <i>make the race</i>— = be in the race 1: He might perhaps consider <u>making the Senate race</u>.</p> </entry>
